      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "TVM IR has the following type cast related operators:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nbuffer.astype(dtype)\r\nT.cast(value, dtype)\r\nT.Cast(dtype, value)\r\n\r\n# And the reinterpret cast operator\r\nT.reinterpret(dtype, value)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe can see that APIs are not very consistent and may cause some confusions. This PR unifies them to:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nbuffer.astype(dtype)\r\nT.cast(value, dtype)\r\n# We don't recommend use T.Cast now. And all examples are refactored to use T.cast\r\nT.reinterpret(value, dtype) # Reorder to consistent with T.cast. Always value first, dtype second\r\n```\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Standardized cast/reinterpret APIs: unified argument order and introduced new cast/reinterpret call forms; compatibility handling added for the old form.\n* **New Features**\n  * Exposed several new public operation aliases in the language bindings for GPU/low-level ops.\n* **Tests / Examples**\n  * Updated tests and examples to adopt the new cast/reinterpret APIs and validate compatibility.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
